    You are given a list of two strings, both strings consist of capable 
     digression " (" or close parentheses ") " merely. 
     Your job is to control if it is potential to concatenate the two string in
     some order, that the result string will be adept. 
     A string S is considered to be good if and only if all parentheses in S
     be balanced. For example: the string "(())()" is good, while the string
    "())" is not.
    Return "Yes" if there"s a way to make a good string, and return "No" otherwise.

